reviewText: Rousey is the best and will probably stay that way for a while.

There were only 2 exciting fights in this show.

Rory Mcdonald vs Demian  Mia
Demian was dominant right from the beginning. In round 1, he took Rory down and landed multiple strikes from above. Consequently, Rorys face was covered in his own blood.
In round 2, Demian tried to take down Rory multiple times but he failed. Rory was dominant in round 2 and 3 but he could not finish off Demian. This fight was worth 4 stars but whole show was worth 3 stars.

Cody Gibson vs Aljamain Sterling
It was a fast paced and intense fight but it became very slow at the end of the first round. It got exciting again in round 2 and 3.

Robert Whittaker vs Stephen Thomson
It ended in round 1. Both of the fighters missed their target many times.

Mike Pyle vs TJ Waldburger
Mike was dominant right from the beginning. It ended in round 3.

Daniel Cormier vs Partrick Cummins
It ended quickly in round 1. Theres no real contest here.

Ronda Rousey vs Sarah Macmann
It ended in round 1 with 3 knees to the liver of Sarah. Theres no real contest here.

Erick Koch vs Rafello Oliveira

Its over in round 1. Theres no real contest here.
Ronda Rousey is the reigning queen of female athletes.  She is real, and just the best.
